Author: buzzer9229
Content:
@everyone Welcome to the server newer Based Indonesians.

Since the beginning of the elections on 2023, I've been prioritizing work over my own mental health and personal relationship. Throughout the year I've lost the people who were important to me and many of my personal relationships were changed as my work continue to change me into a different person. I think you'd understand that feeling of losing people you value over what you think is important to your life's work. And all of that affair has hit me like a bullet train by the end of the elections. I now face the consequences of prioritizing work over my life.

And it has been a really bad impact towards my well being as well as the people around me. I want to focus on myself and the people around me more, and actually build meaningful relationships moving forward. 

Besides that, The Based Indonesian Show is facing changes to its programming and production. We are expected to receive newer additions to the team and better visuals as well as a (finally) well thought out plan of what we want to do in the future. Two new co-host will be introduced to help the Based Indonesian Show, and big names are being contacted in order to appear up in the Based Indonesian Show.

Considering those two factors, the Based Indonesian Show will now slow down in terms of content. I think I will just post one content per week, and shorts depending on the availability of the content. ***I will stream depending on the mood and time, in which I will announce atleast 12 hours before the stream***. Bear in mind that all of these are an attempt to improve the quality of our content. 

But because the Based Indonesian Show is all about its viewers, we want you to tell us what you want! **Tag me and the @Dewan Pengurus to submit the changes you want to see in the Based Indonesian Show!**

Thank you for following our small and humble Based Indonesian Show ğŸ™

Author: buzzer9229
Content:
@everyone Alright guys, I'm gonna do a bit of revamping on the Based(less) Indonesian Show and I think I am going to need some of your input. Let me know what you like to see more on the show:
1. More stuff about our **internal politics** (etc elections, regional government, central government, party politics)
2. More stuff about **international politics** (etc America First, Taiwan, Israel-Palestine, Ukraine, United Nations)
3. **ASEAN dynamics** (etc Indonesia-Malaysia rivalry, why everyone hates Singapore, Vietnam rising)
4. Stuff about **practical and theoretical politics** (etc concept of deterrence, how to bargain, acquiring power and influence)
5. **Pop culture, culture, anime, manga, games, books, films** (etc analyzing the politics of Attack on Titan, explaining House of the Dragon)

React to a number according to what you want to see more. You can have more than one votes. Thank you for your attention guys and have a nice day ğŸ‘

Author: edennottheproject
Content:
***PSA, AGAIN***
@Kader 

There's a difference between venting/sharing your struggles and oversharing in chat!

Please be mindful of your fellow members when you share personal stories. You will be warned if the conversation becomes inappropriare and brings discomfort to fellow members aka bad vibes

Here's a tip, ask yourself these whenever you share things about yourself:

1. Have you interacted with people currently online frequently enough for them to recieve your story well?
Yes? Good keep going
No? Hold it off or DM them

2. Is the thing you're sharing heavy to digest? Is it depressing? Is it sensitive? Is it inappropriate? Will it make people uncomfortable to read and awkward to respond to?
Yes? Take it elsewhere
No? Sure but in moderation pls

3. If minors are presently online, is this something that would be beneficial for them to hear as a lesson in life?
Yes? Sure but mind your language
No? Take it elsewhere

4. Is this NSFW or will lead to NSFW conversation?
Yes? You are breaking the rules

-Mod Team-

Author: edennottheproject
Content:
@everyone 

Hello Kaders!

This server has grown quite rapidly since we started the mod team - it's only been *five months*, could you believe it?

That being said, Server Administrators have decided to open a second round of moderator recruitment, and we hope that potential moderators have the following qualities:

- can commit to active interaction in the server
- has an understanding of mabased server dynamics and operations
- able to host an event / yap in  voice channels, occassionally
- able to handle fights in chat, both casual and political discussions
- respect confidentiality, particularly personal details of members, content creation, and state secrets
- good health and of sound body and mind

If you are interested, please fill out the form by **5 September**. Candidates will be screened on several factors, including **age, chat history, and professionalism**. Following that we will reach out to potential moderators to confirm their interest

Alternatively, you can nominate other people too! Send us your nominations by opening a ticket

Good luck!

-Eden

My chindo brothers and sisters: please be aware rumors have been planted to sow fear among all of us

These unconfirmed rumors and planted messages include:

Whatsapp message broadcasts urging all chinese indonesians to stay inside, now widely forwarded

Kidnappings of two university students in chindo majority universities in Tangerang Selatan, university and time of incident never specified

And various reports of verbal harrasment on the streets of Jakarta

All of this happened in one day, gradually and slowly

We alongside fellow discord members who were monitoring the situation all day have tried to investigate these sources but they are either taken down, suspiciously similar to other sources, or cannot be found

The difficulty with this is that official news media has been ordered to refrain from reporting anything about the events of this week and many such reports have been spreading via word of mouth and social media and thus needed to be investigated via social media as well..

If you see any of these please take extreme precautions and verify them yourself before forwarding them.

The fight was never about the race, it's always about the regime

***Eden***

Dear @Kader 

Mod team would like to salute all of you for your efforts in monitoring the situation and being conscious of the developing situation

That being said Eden would like to add that the above announcement may not be true and would like to apologise for this mistake - let us chalk it as the worst example of a fearmongering hoax.

However because the location and time is of sensitive nature it would not be wise to not share this either

Today has been a long day, too many things are happening and Mod team are trying their best to make sure everyone goes through this calmly - it's our first time too!

Please take a break when you can, don't spend too many hours on discord. Just because we have compiled the information and filtered out the hoaxes still means that it is still a form of doomscrolling.

For the members who contribute to helping us moderate the chat, calling out other members for typing in the wrong chat, and sending information and links, we thank you alot

For the courageous members who went down on the field today, the server thanks you for your bravery and showing us the reality of the streets to counter the feamongering on social media

Get your 10 hours of sleep kaders, good night.

Eden

Author: buzzer9229
Content:
@everyone Haven't dropped a video in a hot minute, I owe you guys an explanation. 

-Since the August protests I've been wrought with disappointment and I was disillusioned by the politics. This became an obstacle to my creative process and I threw myself mostly in work around September which is why I barely posted anything.
-Since going to Korea in August, I have been experiencing coughs and wheezing. Around October 14th, after spending the entire day outside to attend my friend's birthday party, I woke up the next day with a high fever. I drank some meds hoping that the symptoms would go away but the symptoms worsened and I spent 5 days in a feverish condition, a terrible fever and headache I can barely get any sleep. I stubbornly refused to go to the doctors thinking it was flu and continued my work, and day by day it went away but I had a terrible cough and flu. Suddenly it was getting really hard for me to breath and I was weak most of the time. The doctors said I had chronic bronchitis and that the airways on my right lung is filled with mucus and was inflammed, making breathing hard and cardio related activities difficult.
-Around two weeks ago, a member of my family got typhus and I had to stay and look after them in the hospital for a week, baring me from any work or content related matters.
-It's hard for me to stream or produce content at night because I'm focusing on trying to apply for master's degree. And the process is tedious. I was working on my GRE, my IELTS, my WES, and 11 university application simultaneously between the periods of September till now.

That's why I haven't dropped a video for a while but I really wanted to talk about the SMA 72 case which I think deserves more attention since it has something to do with the direction of our youth and education. Around mid December, I think I will be more freer to do more content and hopefully we can get that offline meetup I promised you guys.

https://youtu.be/t1SeseuVsHQ?si=5WbBa1RwLIFONh7O

Author: edennottheproject
Content:
# SERVER ANNOUNCEMENT

we have just banned Stonky in both G space, Mabased, and WIUI. If you have not noticed, she has been a very prominent contributor to the chats in the server but however lately we have seen one too many instances of her fighting the chat, bullying her, and influencing the big chat to ostracise and isolate the member. On this oversight, we apologise for waiting so long to take action

last month, the moderation team was approached with a random account, who has dmed us with messages from our personal mod chat
the account insinuates that they have hacked our server, read through our messages, and sent it to us as blackmail, intending to make mods suspect and hate each other

we have banned this member from wiui and mabased - since i am moderating both

we spent most of the last month investigating in a private group chat who this person might be

following that, in response to recent fights stonky has had with members, she was requested to lay off, cool down, and improve her behavior. however this was not followed, and therefore server owners have decided to not only talk her down, but ban her. this explains the weird baby gif out of nowhere

using an alt account that she had used in wiui under another name
stonky, after being fired - she was fired, by the way, because she banned a member without due process and consensus - and a week later somehow hacked the server to read messages that were sent after her firing, and that was part of the blackmail that we recieved

mods have approached certain members who have fought with stonky to garner information. in the process, the realisation of the alt's identity came when tracking down chat logs from stonk's known alias in wiui only to see that it was indeed the name of the hacker

IF YOU ARE RECIEVING MESSAGES FROM THESE PEOPLE:
GUNKLEDUNKLE / COSMEEW / DONTNUX 

DO NOT ENGAGE. DONT TELL THEM ANYTHING FROM THIS NOTICE

Author: gksubrata
Content:
Just a friendly reminder to all @Kader 

Iâ€™ve noticed that there has been a lot of current issues that concerns a lot of us here and it may have caused a lot of stress. Updating the news here is a part of this serverâ€™s purpose to let the community speak their take on the situation.

However, 

It is understandable that some might see it as a stress inducing conundrum. Some might choose not to read, some might even chose to rant their frustration out on the current takes, and thatâ€™s alright.

So, as a friendly nudge to us, if the news here or the discussions here are too stressing, I urge us to focus on the things we can control. Because the news isnâ€™t going to change just because we want it to be no matter how bad we want it. Because itâ€™s out of our control.

Instead, pay attention to your own well being and do the things that can calm your nerves. Whether it be streaming your gameplays, watching your movies, or just hang in a call if you want to.

If the members really want to speak about the current events, **please keep it in the** #âŠ±ãƒ»ğŸ—ºï¸ãƒ»international-discussion **or** #âŠ±ãƒ»ğŸ“°ãƒ»global-news 

This is a communal space, please respect the needs and wants of one another.

Thank you
